title: Use readLines instead of readText
message:
Use readLines instead of readText

On some devices, readText() on /proc/* returns empty string because proc files has no length.
bufferedReader can get proc contents since that reads by static bytes from file for buffering.
readLines() uses bufferedReader internally so this works well.

cf. https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29874941/elixir-file-read-returns-empty-data-when-accessing-proc-cpuinfo
